1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 4.1-01 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to a low-carbon fuels fund; to amend and reenact sections 39-04-39 and
3 54-44.5-09 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to the distribution of certain vehicle
4 registration fees and ethanol production incentives; to repeal chapter 17-02 of the North Dakota
5 Century Code, relating to ethanol production incentives; to provide a continuing appropriation;
6 to provide for a transfer; and to provide for a report.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
8 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 4.1-01 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
9 and enacted as follows:
10 Low - carbon fuels fund - Continuing appropriation .
11 1. The low - carbon fuels fund is created as a special fund in the state treasury. The fund
12 consists of all moneys transferred to the fund under section 39 - 04 - 39. The moneys in
13 the fund are appropriated to the commissioner on a continuing basis to distribute
14 low - carbon fuels incentives and carbon intensity verification under this section .
15 2. The commissioner shall distribute low - carbon fuels incentives to ethanol production
16 facilities for eligible capital projects that increase the efficiency of a facility and
17 decrease the carbon intensity of the production process. Distributions of low - carbon
18 fuels incentives to an ethanol production facility are limited to fifty percent of the cost
19 of eligible capital projects and may not exceed:
20 a. Three million dollars per biennium;
21 b. Cumulative distributions of ten million dollars per facility; and
22 c. A period of ten years beginning with the first distribution to the facility.
23 3. For purposes of this section, "eligible capital projects" means construction of new
24 infrastructure or replacement of existing infrastructure for carbon dioxide capture and
